"The Internet of Things (IoT) – for so long the favourite topic when experts and pundits discussed future trends – is now upon us. From toys to cars, TVs to trains, embedded microprocessors and computers are being hooked up to the Internet as a way of providing extra functionality. But who is thinking about security? In this interview, we talk to Cesare Garlati, chief security strategist for the prpl Foundation, a consortium for the tech industry that is trying to answer that question with, “we are”."
